cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is about improving neural machine translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses various methods for generating synthetic data, which involves machine learning techniques such as sampling and beam search, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely sub-category as well. Additionally, the paper uses large amounts of data and achieves state-of-the-art results, indicating that it may also fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions studying domain effects, which could potentially fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision) if the domains involve visual data.
